05/04/2005
ROME, Italy -- Several Balkan leaders announced on Monday (4 April) that they would attend the funeral of Pope John Paul II. Albanian President Alfred Moisiu and Prime Minister Fatos Nano, Bulgarian President Georgi Parvanov, Kosovo President Ibrahim Rugova, Romanian President Traian Basescu and Prime Minister Calin Popescu Tariceanu will travel to the Vatican on Friday, joining Western leaders for the funeral.
Meanwhile, the foreign ministers of the Adriatic Charter countries -- Albania, Croatia and Macedonia -- are meeting in Durres, Albania on Tuesday to discuss ongoing efforts to join Euro-Atlantic structures. Their counterparts from Germany, Bosnia and Herzegovina and Serbia-Montenegro are attending as well. (Makfax - 05/04/05; CBS, AP, ATA, Tanjug - 04/04/05)
